data: Marzia Rosati Nuclear My field of is Experimental Nuclear Physics, focusing on Relativistic Heavy Ion Collisions. I participate in the PHENIX experiment at RHIC at Brookhaven National Laboratory. My interest is to study quarkonium and heavy flavor production in relativistic heavy ion collisions. A list of recent publications can be found from the inspire database. mrosati@iastate.edu 515-294-8573 Ph.D., McGill University, 1992
